<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit III Q1 — Free module definition</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[An \(R\)-module \(M\) is called free if:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: \(M\) has a basis (a linearly independent spanning set).</strong><br>A basis \(\{e_i\}\) of a free \(R\)-module satisfies: (i) every element is a finite \(R\)-linear combination of basis elements, and (ii) if \(\sum r_i e_i=0\) then all \(r_i=0\). Free modules are exactly the modules isomorphic to \(R^n\) (for finite rank) or \(R^{(I)}\) (for infinite rank).</p>]]></text>
  </generalfeedback>
