<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit III Q2 — Structure theorem for fg modules over PID</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[The structure theorem for finitely generated modules over a PID \(R\) states that every such module \(M\) is isomorphic to:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: A direct sum \(R^r\oplus R/d_1R\oplus\cdots\oplus R/d_kR\) where \(d_1\mid d_2\mid\cdots\mid d_k\).</strong><br>Here \(r\ge 0\) is the free rank and \(d_1,\ldots,d_k\) are the invariant factors (non-units, each dividing the next). This decomposition is unique. The torsion part is \(R/d_1R\oplus\cdots\oplus R/d_kR\).</p>]]></text>
  </generalfeedback>
