<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit III Q3 — Submodule of free module over PID</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[Every submodule of a finitely generated free module over a PID is:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: Free.</strong><br>If \(F\cong R^n\) is free over a PID \(R\) and \(N\subseteq F\) is a submodule, then \(N\) is free of rank \(\le n\). This generalises the fact that subgroups of free abelian groups \(\mathbb{Z}^n\) are free abelian. The proof uses induction on rank and the fact that submodules of \(R^1=R\) are ideals, which in a PID are free of rank \(\le 1\).</p>]]></text>
  </generalfeedback>
