<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit III Q5 — Number of abelian groups of order 72</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[The number of non-isomorphic abelian groups of order \(72=2^3\cdot 3^2\) is:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: 6.</strong><br>By the fundamental theorem of finitely generated abelian groups, the number equals the product of the number of partitions of each prime-power exponent. Partitions of 3 (for \(2^3\)): \((3),(2,1),(1,1,1)\) — 3 types. Partitions of 2 (for \(3^2\)): \((2),(1,1)\) — 2 types. Total: \(3\times 2=6\) non-isomorphic abelian groups.</p>]]></text>
  </generalfeedback>
