<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit III Q6 — Schur's Lemma</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[Schur's Lemma states that if \(M\) and \(N\) are simple \(R\)-modules, then every \(R\)-module homomorphism \(f:M\to N\) is:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: Either zero or an isomorphism.</strong><br>Since \(M\) is simple, \(\ker f\) is either \(0\) or \(M\). Since \(N\) is simple, \(\mathrm{im}(f)\) is either \(0\) or \(N\). If \(f\ne 0\), then \(\ker f=0\) and \(\mathrm{im}(f)=N\), making \(f\) an isomorphism. In particular, \(\mathrm{End}_R(M)\) is a division ring.</p>]]></text>
  </generalfeedback>
