<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit III Q7 — Invariant factor decomposition</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[The abelian group \(\mathbb{Z}^2/H\) where \(H\) is generated by \((4,0)\) and \((0,6)\) is isomorphic to:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: \(\mathbb{Z}/2\mathbb{Z}\oplus\mathbb{Z}/12\mathbb{Z}\).</strong><br>The presentation matrix is \(\begin{pmatrix}4&0\\0&6\end{pmatrix}\). Smith Normal Form: \(d_1=\gcd(4,6)=2\), determinant \(=24\), so \(d_2=24/2=12\). SNF is \(\begin{pmatrix}2&0\\0&12\end{pmatrix}\). Hence \(\mathbb{Z}^2/H\cong\mathbb{Z}/2\mathbb{Z}\oplus\mathbb{Z}/12\mathbb{Z}\).</p>]]></text>
  </generalfeedback>
