<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit III Q10 — Projective module</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[An \(R\)-module \(P\) is projective if and only if:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: \(P\) is a direct summand of a free module.</strong><br>Equivalently, \(P\) is projective iff every surjection \(f:M\to P\) splits (has a section). Over a PID, projective modules are free. Over more general rings, there exist projective non-free modules (e.g., non-principal ideals in Dedekind domains).</p>]]></text>
  </generalfeedback>
