<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit III Q11 — Torsion submodule</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[The torsion submodule \(T(M)\) of an \(R\)-module \(M\) over an integral domain \(R\) is:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: \(\{m\in M: rm=0\text{ for some non-zero }r\in R\}\).</strong><br>\(T(M)\) is indeed a submodule (since \(R\) is an integral domain, if \(r_1 m_1=0\) and \(r_2 m_2=0\) then \(r_1r_2(m_1\pm m_2)=0\)). If \(M=T(M)\), \(M\) is a torsion module; if \(T(M)=0\), \(M\) is torsion-free. Over a PID, a finitely generated torsion-free module is free.</p>]]></text>
  </generalfeedback>
