<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit III Q12 — Hom_R(R,M)</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[For any \(R\)-module \(M\), the module \(\mathrm{Hom}_R(R,M)\) is isomorphic to:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: \(M\).</strong><br>An \(R\)-module homomorphism \(f:R\to M\) is completely determined by \(f(1)\in M\) (since \(f(r)=rf(1)\)). This gives a bijection \(\mathrm{Hom}_R(R,M)\cong M\) via \(f\mapsto f(1)\). This is a special case of the Yoneda Lemma.</p>]]></text>
