<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit III Q13 — Finitely generated torsion-free module over PID</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[A finitely generated torsion-free module over a PID is:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: Free.</strong><br>By the structure theorem, a finitely generated module \(M\) over a PID decomposes as \(R^r\oplus T\) where \(T\) is the torsion part. If \(M\) is torsion-free, then \(T=0\), so \(M\cong R^r\) is free. This is the key result: over PIDs, finitely generated + torsion-free \(\Leftrightarrow\) free.</p>]]></text>
  </generalfeedback>
