<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit III Q14 — Rational canonical form</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[The rational canonical form of a linear operator \(T:V\to V\) over a field \(F\) is determined by:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: The invariant factors of \(V\) as an \(F[x]\)-module (where \(x\) acts by \(T\)).</strong><br>Making \(V\) an \(F[x]\)-module via \(T\), the structure theorem gives \(V\cong F[x]/(f_1)\oplus\cdots\oplus F[x]/(f_k)\) with \(f_1\mid f_2\mid\cdots\mid f_k\). The companion matrices of \(f_1,\ldots,f_k\) form the blocks of the rational canonical form.</p>]]></text>
