<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>CSIR PYQ Unit III Q15 — Simple module</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[An \(R\)-module \(M\ne 0\) is simple if and only if:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: \(M\cong R/\mathfrak{m}\) for some maximal left ideal \(\mathfrak{m}\) of \(R\).</strong><br>Every non-zero element \(m\in M\) generates \(M\) (since \(Rm\) is a non-zero submodule of simple \(M\), so \(Rm=M\)). The map \(r\mapsto rm\) is surjective with kernel \(\mathrm{Ann}(m)\), a maximal left ideal. Conversely \(R/\mathfrak{m}\) is simple for maximal \(\mathfrak{m}\).</p>]]></text>
