  <questiontext format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[A matrix \(A\) over a field \(F\) has a Jordan normal form over \(F\) if and only if:]]></text>
  </questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: The characteristic polynomial of \(A\) splits completely over \(F\).</strong><br>Jordan normal form exists over \(F\) iff all eigenvalues lie in \(F\), i.e., \(\det(\lambda I-A)\) splits as a product of linear factors over \(F\). Every matrix over \(\mathbb{C}\) has Jordan form (since \(\mathbb{C}\) is algebraically closed). Over \(\mathbb{R}\), only matrices with all real eigenvalues have Jordan form over \(\mathbb{R}\).</p>]]></text>
