  <generalfeedback format="html">
    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: The largest invariant factor (the generator of \(\mathrm{Ann}_{F[x]}(V)\)).</strong><br>Viewing \(V\) as an \(F[x]\)-module via \(T\), the minimal polynomial \(m_T(x)\) is the monic generator of the annihilator ideal \(\mathrm{Ann}_{F[x]}(V)=\{f\in F[x]:f(T)=0\}\). In the invariant factor decomposition \(V\cong F[x]/(f_1)\oplus\cdots\oplus F[x]/(f_k)\) with \(f_1\mid\cdots\mid f_k\), the minimal polynomial is \(f_k\).</p>]]></text>
