    <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: \(M\cong\bigoplus_p M(p)\) where \(M(p)=\{m\in M: p^km=0\text{ for some }k\}\) is the \(p\)-primary component.</strong><br>Each \(M(p)\) is the submodule of elements annihilated by a power of the prime \(p\). This is the primary (or Sylow) decomposition of \(M\), and each \(M(p)\) decomposes further as \(R/p^{a_1}R\oplus\cdots\oplus R/p^{a_r}R\).</p>]]></text>
  </generalfeedback>
